A fork of the luasyslog-1.0.0-2 add-on by Nicolas Casalini found in the
luarocks main repository (http://luarocks.org/).

The planned/implemented enhancements include Lua 5.2 support, a revamped
build system and proper module encapsulation.


Installation
============

Available targets, usable with "make TARGET":

* all (default): compile C module
* dist: generate luasyslog-*.tar.gz
* check: run test.lua, logging some message with syslog
* rock: build the .src.rock package
* rockspec: generate luasyslog-*-1.rockspeck
* install: install everything
* install-cmod: install the C module
* install-lmod: install the Lua script
* uninstall: uninstall all installed files
* clean: remove files generated by "make all"
* clean-rock: remove files generated by "make rock"
* distclean: remove any generated file
